<scope ilk="blob" lang="PHP" name="ip_in_range.php" src="/private/var/www/kw/plugins/w3-total-cache/inc/functions/ip_in_range.php"><scope doc="decbin32&#10;In order to simplify working with IP addresses (in binary) and their&#10;netmasks, it is easier to ensure that the binary strings are padded&#10;with zeros out to 32 characters - IP addresses are 32 bit numbers" ilk="function" line="40" lineend="42" name="w3_decbin32" returns="str_pad()" signature="w3_decbin32($dec)"><variable ilk="argument" line="40" name="dec" /></scope><scope doc="ipv4_in_range&#10;This function takes 2 arguments, an IP address and a &quot;range&quot; in several&#10;different formats.&#10;Network ranges can be specified as:&#10;1. Wildcard format:     1.2.3.*&#10;2. CIDR format:         1.2.3/24  OR  1.2.3.4/255.255.255.0&#10;3. Start-End IP format: 1.2.3.0-1.2.3.255&#10;The function will return true if the supplied IP is within the range.&#10;Note little validation is done on the range inputs - it expects you to&#10;use one of the above 3 formats." ilk="function" line="54" lineend="100" name="w3_ipv4_in_range" returns="boolean" signature="w3_ipv4_in_range($ip, $range)"><variable ilk="argument" line="54" name="ip" /><variable ilk="argument" line="54" name="range" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="68" name="b" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="68" name="c" /><variable citdl="int" line="94" name="upper_dec" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="68" name="a" /><variable citdl="pow()" line="77" name="wildcard_dec" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="68" name="d" /><variable citdl="str_replace()" line="86" name="lower" /><variable citdl="ip2long()" line="70" name="range_dec" /><variable citdl="ip2long()" line="71" name="ip_dec" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" citdl="str_replace()" line="57" name="netmask" /><variable citdl="int" line="93" name="lower_dec" /><variable citdl="explode()" line="66" name="x" /><variable citdl="ip2long()" line="61" name="netmask_dec" /><variable citdl="str_replace()" line="87" name="upper" /></scope><scope ilk="function" line="102" lineend="114" name="w3_ip2long6" returns="base_convert()" signature="w3_ip2long6($ip)"><variable ilk="argument" line="102" name="ip" /><variable citdl="string" line="108" name="r_ip" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="109" name="v" /></scope><scope doc="Get the ipv6 full format and return it as a decimal value." ilk="function" line="117" lineend="157" name="w3_get_ipv6_full" returns="w3_ip2long6()" signature="w3_get_ipv6_full($ip)"><variable ilk="argument" line="117" name="ip" /><variable citdl="ip_pieces" line="126" name="last_ip_piece" /><variable citdl="ip_pieces" line="125" name="main_ip_piece" /><variable citdl="implode()" line="154" name="final_ip" /><variable citdl="explode()" line="119" name="pieces" /><variable line="141" name="i" /><variable citdl="count()" line="136" name="size" /><variable citdl="explode()" line="124" name="ip_pieces" /><variable citdl="pieces" line="120" name="left_piece" /><variable citdl="string" line="135" name="last_piece" /><variable citdl="pieces" line="121" name="right_piece" /><variable line="130" name="key" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="130" name="val" /><variable citdl="explode()" line="129" name="main_ip_pieces" /></scope><scope doc="Determine whether the IPV6 address is within range.&#10;$ip is the IPV6 address in decimal format to check if its within the IP range created by the cloudflare IPV6 address, $range_ip.&#10;$ip and $range_ip are converted to full IPV6 format.&#10;Returns true if the IPV6 address, $ip,  is within the range from $range_ip.  False otherwise." ilk="function" line="164" lineend="212" name="w3_ipv6_in_range" returns="in_range" signature="w3_ipv6_in_range($ip, $range_ip)"><variable ilk="argument" line="164" name="ip" /><variable ilk="argument" line="164" name="range_ip" /><variable citdl="ip_pieces" line="173" name="last_ip_piece" /